	</header>
	<body>
	
		<section>
							<title>Admin4J Notifiers.</title>
							
							<p>An Admin4J notifier is the mechanism through which Admin4J 'notifies' administrators of
							   detected problems and issues.  All notifiers implement interface net.admin4j.util.notify.Notifier.</p>
							   
							<section>
									<title>Email Notification</title>
									
									<p>Email notification classes:</p>
									<table>
										<tr>
												<td>net.admin4j.util.notify.HtmlEmailNotifier</td>
												<td>Email with HTML format.</td>
										</tr>
										<tr>
												<td>net.admin4j.util.notify.TextEmailNotifier</td>
												<td>Email with Text format.</td>
										</tr>
										<tr>
												<td>net.admin4j.util.notify.SmsTextEmailNotifier</td>
												<td>Email with Text format limited to 70 characters.</td>
										</tr>
									</table>
									
									<p>Email notifier support the following properties, filter parameters, or servlet parameters:</p>
									<table>
											<tr>
												<th>Parameter</th>
												<th>Required</th>
												<th>Default</th>
												<th>Description</th>
										 </tr>
										 <tr>
												<td>mail.server.host</td>
												<td>Y</td>
												<td>none.</td>
												<td>For example 'mail.admin4j.net'.</td>					 
										 </tr>
										 <tr>
												<td>from.email.address</td>
												<td>Y</td>
												<td>none.</td>
												<td>For example 'appName@admin4j.net'.</td>					 
										 </tr>
										 <tr>
												<td>to.email.address</td>
												<td>Y</td>
												<td>none.</td>
												<td>For example 'App_Support@admin4j.net'.</td>					 
										 </tr>
										 <tr>
												<td>allowed.servers</td>
												<td>N</td>
												<td>none.</td>
												<td>Comma delimited list of servers that can send email.</td>					 
										 </tr>
									</table>
							</section>
							
							<section>
									<title>Log Notification</title>
									
									<p>The log notifier class is net.admin4j.util.notify.LogNotifier and currently
									  supports no parameters.  Notification log entries are made to a logger of the
									  same name.</p>
							</section>
		</section>
	
	</body>
